hashCode.name: hashCode
hashCode.comment:
Get a hash code for this object.

All objects have hash codes. Hash codes are guaranteed to be the same for objects that are equal when compared using the equality operator ==. Other than that there are no guarantees about the hash codes. They will not be consistent between runs and there are no distribution guarantees.

If a subclass overrides restlib_common/collections.IndexedIterator.hashCode it should override the equality operator as well to maintain consistency.

runtimeType.name: runtimeType
runtimeType.comment: A representation of the runtime type of the object.

current.name: current
current.comment:
Returns the current element.

Return null if the iterator has not yet been moved to the first element, or if the iterator has been moved after the last element of the dart-core.Iterable.

==.comment:
The equality operator.

The default behavior for all dart-core.Objects is to return true if and only if this and restlib_common/collections.IndexedIterator.==.other are the same object.

Override this method to specify a different equality relation on a class. The overriding method must still be an equivalence relation. That is, it must be:

  • Total: It must return a boolean for all arguments. It should never throw or return null.

  • Reflexive: For all objects o, o == o must be true.

  • Symmetric: For all objects o1 and o2, o1 == o2 and o2 == o1 must either both be true, or both be false.

  • Transitive: For all objects o1, o2, and o3, if o1 == o2 and o2 == o3 are true, then o1 == o3 must be true.

The method should also be consistent over time, so equality of two objects should not change over time, or at least only change if one of the objects was modified.

If a subclass overrides the equality operator it should override the restlib_common/collections.IndexedIterator.hashCode method as well to maintain consistency.

toString.name: toString
toString.comment: Returns a string representation of this object.

noSuchMethod.name: noSuchMethod
noSuchMethod.comment:
restlib_common/collections.IndexedIterator.noSuchMethod is invoked when users invoke a non-existent method on an object. The name of the method and the arguments of the invocation are passed to restlib_common/collections.IndexedIterator.noSuchMethod in an dart-core.Invocation. If restlib_common/collections.IndexedIterator.noSuchMethod returns a value, that value becomes the result of the original invocation.

The default behavior of restlib_common/collections.IndexedIterator.noSuchMethod is to throw a dart-core.NoSuchMethodError.

moveNext.name: moveNext
moveNext.comment:
Moves to the next element. Returns true if restlib_common/collections.IndexedIterator.current contains the next element. Returns false, if no element was left.

It is safe to invoke restlib_common/collections.IndexedIterator.moveNext even when the iterator is already positioned after the last element. In this case restlib_common/collections.IndexedIterator.moveNext has no effect.

movePrevious.name: movePrevious
movePrevious.comment:
Move back to the previous element.

Returns true and updates current if successful. Returns false and sets current to null if there is no previous element.
